Thought process
Thought process
Good catch — this is where Notion falls short. TikTok's verification is file-based: it gives you a signature file to download, and you have to make that exact file reachable at your URL. Notion's notion.site domain is shared platform infrastructure — you don't get to place arbitrary files at arbitrary paths there, so verification will never pass on a Notion link.

You need hosting where you control the actual file structure. GitHub Pages is the standard free option for this:

Go to github.com, sign in (or sign up free if you don't have an account).
Create a new public repository, e.g. unison-clips-legal.
Add privacy.html and terms.html to it (paste your policy text wrapped in basic HTML tags), and commit.
In the repo, go to Settings → Pages, set "Source" to the main branch / root folder, and save. After ~1 minute, your files are live at:
https://<your-username>.github.io/unison-clips-legal/privacy.html
https://<your-username>.github.io/unison-clips-legal/terms.html
Put those two URLs into TikTok's Privacy Policy URL / Terms of Service URL fields, and save.
Back on the app page, click "Verify URL properties" → choose "URL prefix" (not Domain — you don't own the github.io domain itself, only your specific repo path) → enter the full URL (e.g. the privacy.html one) → TikTok gives you a signature file to download.
Add that exact signature file to the same GitHub repo (same commit/push flow as step 3), so it's reachable at the path TikTok expects. Then click Verify.
Repeat step 6–7 for the second URL (Terms of Service), and for your Web/Desktop site URL if TikTok asks for one too — each gets its own signature file, placed in the same repo.
If you don't already use GitHub and want something even faster with zero git commands, Netlify Drop (app.netlify.com/drop) works the same way — you drag a folder of files into the browser and get a live URL where you fully control the file paths, so the same signature-file step works there too. Let me know which one you'd rather use and I can tailor the exact file names for you once you're at that step.

